Description: An X11-only, lighter-weight fork of KWin - devel files
 sonic-win is an X11 window manager and a compositing manager.
 Its primary usage is in conjunction with a Desktop Shell
 (e.g. sonic-desktop) sonic-win is designed to stay out of the way;
 users should not notice that they use a window manager at all.
 Nevertheless sonic-win provides a steep learning curve for
 advanced features, which are available, if they do not conflict
 with the primary mission. sonic-win does not have a dedicated targeted
 user group, but follows the targeted user group of the Desktop
 Shell using sonic-win as it's window manager.
 .
